description: A unique identifier for a unit within a catalog.
A text string describing the name of the cataloger, in any chosen format.
comments: NULL values are allowed to support legacy data, but are not recommended.

description: Auto-incrementing surrogate primary key.
Key to the event during which this unit was cataloged.
An identifier assigned by the collector to this collected unit at the collecting event.
Auto-incrementing surrogate primary key.
Key to the collecting event in which this collected unit was generated.

An identifier assigned by the collector to this collecting event, this might be called a field number or a station number or a collector number. The identifier applies to all the material collected during that same event.
A text describing the name(s) of the collector(s) in any chosen format. Can be persons and/or organisations or groups.
Key to this collecting event’s event.
Auto-incrementing surrogate primary key.
The integer day of the month on which the event started.
The integer month on which the event ended.
The integer year on which the event ended.
A text describing when this event took place in any chosen format.
Auto-incrementing surrogate primary key.
A text string describing where an event took place, in any chosen format.
The integer day of the month on which the event started.
The integer month on which the event started.
The integer year on which the event started.
Key to the cataloged unit to which this identifiable unit belongs.
Key to the physical unit to which this identifiable unit belongs.
Auto-incrementing surrogate primary key.
A text describing this identifiable unit, in any chosen format. For example it’s location in relation to other identifiable units.
example_values: ”In the lower left corner of the slide”, ”The moss (bright green), not the lichen”

description: Key to the individual group this identifiable unit is represented by.
Key to the identifiable unit that is a parent of this identifiable unit.
Auto-incrementing surrogate primary key.
A boolean value indicating whether the identification is the original determination made by the collector(s).
Key to his identification’s observation.
An integer, starting at 1, indicating the relative position in time for the identification event. The latest event has the highest value.
Auto-incrementing surrogate primary key.
An integer representing the number of individuals in this individual group.
A text describing this individual group, in any chosen format.
A defined type of individual group.
comments: Allowed values: ”single individual”, ”multiple individuals”, ”unknown number of individuals”

description: A text description of the life history for this individual group.
Auto-incrementing surrogate primary key.
Key to the collected unit that this material was derived from.
An integer representing the number of parts in this material sample.
comments: There may be a need to count parts of different types in a future model.

description: A text with the name of a defined parts type for this material sample.
comments: There may be a need to distinguish parts of different types in a future model. In this version a new material sample must be created.

description: Key to this material sample’s physical unit.
Auto-incrementing surrogate primary key.
Key to the collecting_event to which this observation apply.
Key to the individual group to which this observation apply.
Auto-incrementing surrogate primary key.
A boolean indicating whether an observation is current or not.
Key to the transcribed content in which this observation is documented.
Key to the observation_type that this observation is of.
A text string describing the observation, in any chosen format.
A text describing the agent(s) (person(s), group(s), machine(s) etc.) that made an observation, in any chosen format.
Key to the event during which this observation was made.
The name of the entity to which this observation type applies.
comments: Allowed values: entities in the DINA collections data model.

description: Auto-incrementing surrogate primary key.
A text with the name of a defined observation type.
Auto-incrementing surrogate primary key.
A text string with the name of a defined physical unit type.
A text describing the compound type of preparation for  this physical unit including it’s descendants.
A text describing the agent(s) (person(s), group(s), etc.) that created this preparation, in any chosen format.
The date when this physical unit was created.
comments: May be moved to separat table ”treatment event” later.

description: A text describing the history of this physical unit, in any chosen format.
A text describing the normal physical storage location, in any chosen format.
comments: Will be moved and/or complemented with a storage table,

description: Key to the physical unit to which this transaction unit belongs.
Auto-incrementing surrogate primary key.
Auto-incrementing surrogate primary key.
Key to the transcribed content type that this transcribed content is of.
A text that has been transcribed from any kind of original source (labels, field notebooks, phone calls, emails, etc.)
example_values: ”F. vesiculosus”, ”F. vesiculosus L.S. 21 S. Stavsudda, 1:a juli på stranden”

description: Auto-incrementing surrogate primary key.
A text with the name of a defined transcribed content type.
